BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-08T101551.202.png
CATEGORIES:Talks,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260421T092351Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credit: Rustam Vania\n\nAt the top of the high-altitude Himalayan ranges lives the snow leopard\, elusive and solitary\, known as the ghost of the mountains. To protect it is to protect the fragile world it moves through. \n\nThis illustrated talk and interactive workshop takes you into that world\, tracing the delicate balance between human livelihoods\, conservation\, and the restoration of Himalayan ecosystems.\n\n&nbsp\;\n\nPlease note the interactive workshop has a few slots and requires registration. The illustrated talk\, open for all\, is from 7:00 PM to 8:30 PM.
DTEND:20260505T150000Z
DTSTART:20260505T123000Z
SUMMARY:The Ghosts of Conservation - Political Ecology of High Altitude Himalayan Landscapes
UID:1248@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/the-ghosts-of-conservation-political-ecology-of-high-altitude-himalayan-landscapes/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new.png
CATEGORIES:Listening Session,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260429T071539Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special listening session around the Grindmill Songs Projectand Songs of the Rann\, by the People's Archive of Rural India (PARI)\, which brings together sound\, memory\, and conversation. Facilitated by Namita Waikar and Pratishtha\, this session explores songs as intimate emotional archives—voices that carry lived histories of women’s labour\, resilience\, longing\, humour\, and dissent. \n\nSung while performing everyday work\, these songs reveal how labour\, caste\, gender\, and patriarchy are woven into daily life\, while also creating spaces of expression and solidarity. Through collective listening and discussion\, we will reflect on the power of oral traditions and informal cultural transmission in preserving stories and sustaining memory across generations.\n\n\n\nThis event is part of programming around Beneath the Turning Sky in collaboration with People’s Archives of Rural India (PARI)\n\n\n\n
DTEND:20260516T073000Z
DTSTART:20260516T053000Z
SUMMARY:Songs of Labour: Living Archives
UID:1261@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/songs-of-labour-living-archives/
END:VEVENT
