ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-01T155341.726.png
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260406
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260509
CATEGORIES:Series,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260410T023206Z
DESCRIPTION:A series of faculty-led sessions in the form of talks\, lectures or workshops are delivered by faculty members of Srishti Manipal Institute of Art\, Design &amp\; Technology. These sessions range from sounds\, urban biodiversity\, metaphor-making\, livelihoods\, ecosystems and more.\n\nSchedule\nApril 7\nOn Seeing the Sound in a Changing Environment by Dr Guruaja\, K. V.\n\nApril 18\nWhere Have all the Sparrows Gone? by Aparna Raman\n\nApril 21\nSlow Disturbances by Priya Joseph\n\nApril 25\nClimate Metaphors by Asmita Sarkar\n\nMay 5\nThe Ghosts of Conservation by Rustam Vania\n\nMay 9\nClimate Canvases by Dr Chandrima Home and Dr Sambita Modak\n\nPlease note: Each session requires individual registration. Some sessions require you to bring certain materials so please be prepared.
SUMMARY:Learning Lounge
UID:1238@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/learning-lounge/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/1440-X-810-Widget-03.jpg
CATEGORIES:Film Screenings,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260429T071547Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a screening of documentary films by People's Archive of Rural India (PARI) that bring into focus the intertwined realities of climate change\, gender\, and labour across rural India. Through intimate and powerful storytelling\, these films trace how shifting ecologies reshape livelihoods\, deepen existing inequalities\, and place disproportionate burdens on women and marginalised communities. \n\nFrom farms and forests to coastlines and homes\, the screenings reveal stories of resilience\, adaptation\, and collective action in the face of environmental change. This programme invites audiences to reflect on climate justice not as an abstract future concern\, but as a lived present shaped by work\, care\, and survival.\n\n\n\nThis event is part of programming around Beneath the Turning Sky in collaboration with People’s Archives of Rural India (PARI)\n\n\n\n
DTEND:20260516T103000Z
DTSTART:20260516T093000Z
SUMMARY:Changing Landscapes: Films on Climate\, Gender & Labour
UID:1263@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/changing-landscapes-films-on-climate-gender-labour/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-22T092946.933.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260422T044230Z
DESCRIPTION:A session that moves from gallery to garden.\nBegin with a guided walkthrough of Paper Gardens \, before stepping into the Living Botanical installation with its gardener\, Kush Sethi. Drawing connections between the artworks and the plants around you\, Kush will guide you through observing species\, forms\, compositions\, and the quiet details of plant anatomy.\nThe session then transitions into a hands-on gardening workshop\, slow-paced and unhurried\, where you will practise the art of potting and composing. A gentle introduction to becoming a plant parent.\nYour completed piece is yours to take home.
DTEND:20260509T103000Z
DTSTART:20260509T090000Z
SUMMARY:Plant Parenting 101
UID:1259@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/plant-parenting-101/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-22T104009.698.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260422T140824Z
DESCRIPTION:What does vulnerability look like? What does care feel like?\nThese are the questions that artist Afra Eisma leaves us with in warrior garments.\n\nJoin us for a three-part series of reflective feminist reading sessions\, developed in collaboration with Zubaan and  facilitated by Laxmi Murthy. Together\, we will explore gender-based violence—its lived realities\, and the possibilities of resistance\, solidarity\, and healing. Through stories\, essays\, and personal reflections\, you are invited to engage with the exhibition at your own pace\, in a space that encourages listening\, sharing\, and care.\n\nNote:\n\n-This is the first session in a three-part series presented alongside Warrior Garments. Each session is self-contained\, but we encourage participants to attend all three.\n\n-The upcoming sessions will take place on May 30 and June 21\, 2026.\n\n-Reading materials for each will be shared after registration.\n\nTrigger Warning: The sessions may include discussions on sexual violence.
DTEND:20260502T073000Z
DTSTART:20260502T053000Z
SUMMARY:Holding Space: Feminist Reading Circle
UID:1260@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/holding-space-feminist-reading-circle/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/nature-art-workshop-iisc-2024-scaled-e1775708092836.jpg
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260416T053429Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credit: Dr Sambita Modak\n\nThrough this workshop\, we will connect the audience to the impacts of climate change on ecosystems and how these impacts affect the series of socio-economic linkages around us. The session will focus on three key lenses: biodiversity\, food and water systems\, and social fabric\, connecting these through storytelling and data visualisation. \n\nThrough art explorations\, we will examine themes such as climate grief\, climate injustice\, and the interconnection between them and ecosystems.
DTEND:20260509T140000Z
DTSTART:20260509T103000Z
